                    <p class="secondary-heading c4-text">Our Curriculum</p>
                
<p class="heading main c3-text">Building Americans</p>
                    <div class="text ">
                        <p><span>E.D. Hirsch wrote in his book, <span style="text-decoration: underline;">In The Making of Americans</span>, that there are two central reasons for public education in America:  </span><span>(1) to create social mobility, allowing bright, hard-working students of all backgrounds to have the opportunity of the American dream; and </span><span>(2) to create social cohesion, binding children of diverse economic, racial, and ethnic backgrounds into citizens of a single nation.  </span></p>
<p><span>We celebrate the diversity of cultural backgrounds that have been brought together into the great American melting pot; and we strive to focus on the uniquely American ideals, history, culture, and Constitutional principals that bind us together as a nation. </span></p>
<p><span>Guided by this Vision, our Board of Directors and staff take great care to research and utilize curricular materials that will afford our students the greatest possible educational advantage. All of the curriculum and materials used comply with </span><a rel="noopener" href="http://www.sde.idaho.gov/site/content_standards/" target="_blank">content standards</a><span> established by the Idaho State Department of Education.</span></p>
<p>Get to know the foundation of our curriculum, right from the source.</p>
